        <article role="article" class="h-entry h-as-note hentry note feed-note " id="note-4uzLot">
  <div class="note-body">

    <div class="p-name entry-title p-summary summary e-content">
      <p>[biquad~] clicks and pops when changing coefficients, which is annoying when they‚Äôre coming from the [filterview] UI. The best way I found of smoothing them was to alternate between two biquad~ objects and crossfade between them over 3ms. This approach, while a little cludgy, is probably generalisable to a lot of similar Pd situations where smooth transitions are desirable.</p>

<p><img class="u-photo" src="https://waterpigs.co.uk/img/screen-shot-2018-06-17-at-194348.png" alt="" /></p>


<a href="http://brid.gy/publish/facebook"></a>

<a href="http://brid.gy/publish/twitter"></a>   </div>


